Claudio Foti, the “Lupo di Bibbiano”, acquitted by all charges >maturated in one of the most mediaetic investigations of recent years, and on the other side of the phone there is his lawyer, Luca Bauccio. 'The Wolf of Bibbiano', just like the Milanese criminal titled the book published in the BeHopeBooks Necklace, tells of the trial to the psychotherapist accused of serious personal injury to the damage of a minor patient, of abuse of office and prosecution fraud because it would create false abuse. “The Wolf of Bibbiano – writes in the prolo – is the search for an answer to the elementary question that always comes to be done when an alleged innocent, stoned for years as guilty, is acquitted: why? How was that possible? What errors, what intentions, how much faith and how much malafede have built injustice? What is the evil serum that has subverted every parameter of civilization? ”
Bauccio argues that the answer is in the process cards but also out.&nbsp;
The 'Lupo di Bibbiano', flew in a few days from the exit in the first places of the charts on Amazon to prove how the theme is still 'hot', puts in the view "the terrible > between media and justice, where is precisely justice to the train of improvised influencers of judiciary, executioners of plans that have nothing to do with justice".
It is the era, denounces the author, of the justice of the like. The "subditance by some judges to the podcast Veleno >e to his thesis and reconstructions" is for Bauccio the most eclatating example of "this union where objectivity fades in opinion". &nbsp;
The lawyer is inspired by the genre of the story- document with the intent to reconstruct as in a thriller > the meeting with the customer, the choice of strategy, the defense technique, the decisive meetings, the retroscene.&nbsp; There are dialogues, reconstructions of the environment and private and intimate moments that allow the reader to enter into the process and human affair.&nbsp; "It could be a story already closed. The wolf was just a gentleman with his hair in the air and that disconcerted expression that they have certain 'strizzacervelli'. It could end here but I would like to tell you some details, something that really happened and that makes predict that this story can be repeated.> In a place, context, any time. This partial, disordered, but real story deserves to be told. With eyes, with my mind and mood, the bible wolf lawyer." &nbsp;

